Alhaji Usman Ndalolo, Waziri Patigi in Kwara State is dead. The retired orthopaedic technician and community leader died at the age of 83. Reacting to the sad news, President Muhammadu Buhari on Saturday sent a message of condolence to the government and people of Kwara State. Buhari in the message recalled that the late Ndalolo was a visionary statesman with impeccable integrity and dedication, who will be remembered for his sagacity and exemplary selfless service to the people of Nigeria. In a statement signed by Garba Shehu, the President paid respects to the late Usman Ndalolo and extended sympathies to the bereaved wife, Hajiya Amina Ndalolo, a former Minister of State, Health. He prayed to Almighty Allah to repose his soul